Description:
Delightfully different in sought after location
Full of character and charm, this delightful single level home, will impress from the moment you walk through the front gate. The beautiful garden has been lovingly created and cared for, while the stunning residence has been meticulously renovated and is set to impress.
Offering three bedrooms including master suite with walk through robe and a lovely light filled ensuite. A stunning family bathroom, large laundry and a second living room with open fire offers an inviting room to relax. The open plan kitchen, dining and living area is filled with natural light and opens out through bi-fold and French doors to the entertaining spaces. The kitchen is filled with light and has beautiful concrete benches, great storage and quality Bosch appliances. Ducted heating and evaporative throughout plus open fireplace.
With a choice of two entertainment areas, including a large alfresco deck and a private paved area with pizza oven. If gardens are important, you will appreciate the effort and abundance of mature plants and trees throughout. Water tanks x 3 and garden shed.
Easy rear access into the oversized double garage plus further secure parking behind second roller door from lane.
Walking distance to Geelongs CBD, Garden Street shopping precinct, Geelong High School, our stunning waterfront and only meters from the beautiful Eastern Park and Botanic Gardens. This is a beautiful and quirky home offering a wonderful lifestyle.
For more information on this property text '12 Meakin' to 0428 444 841

Address: 40 Filipi Drive St Albans Park VIC 3219
Description:
ROOM TO GROW WITH MODERN UPDATES
This newly updated brick 3 bed, 2 bath, 2 car property set on a generous 615m2 block has everything you need and more!
Situated in a quiet street, behind a secure front gate this great home would appeal to the savvy investor with a potential rent of $400pw approx, a FHB or a growing family with secure front and back yards to play in.
Being freshly carpeted, painted and fitted with block-out blinds throughout, this newly updated home comprises of spacious front formal living room , equipped with LED downlights and Kaden rev cycle split system for all year round comfort.
The kitchen is the hub of the home and is well equipped with stainless steel Westinghouse 5 burner gas cook top and electric oven and matching Westinghouse range hood. Plus brand new Omega dishwasher and ample cupboard space.
The second smaller living/dining space which comfortably sits 6-8 flows beautifully off the kitchen, featuring a reverse cycle split system which would make for an ideal sitting area.
Down the hall you will find 3 good size bedrooms all with BIR's and block-out blinds. The master offers a 3rd split system for all year round comfort and a handy ensuite bathroom with corner shower, vanity storage, new fittings and brand new toilet.
The main central bathroom offers a separate shower and bath, plus second toilet and functional laundry wet area for all your family needs.
Outside you will be impressed with the spacious undercover side entertaining patio which wraps around to the rear green space and landscaped gardens. The secure front yard is really what sets this home apart from the rest and is a great place for your four legged friend or children can play safely.
This great property is well positioned within close proximity to the local school and parks, public transport nearby and less than 5 mins drive to Geelong CBD and 15 minutes to the Bellarine coast.
FEATURES:
3 x rev cycle split system
Braemar ducted heating
Rent pw $400 approx
Oversized DLUG with access to rear patio
615m2 block approx

Description:
Meticulously Executed and Enticing
Roncon Real Estate presents an enticing opportunity to acquire this amazingly spacious yet low maintenance, neat as a pin three-bedroom home located in the ever-popular Newcomb.
This fully renovated and light filled haven enjoys three sizable bedrooms; one with built in robes. The bathroom includes shower; with a separate toilet neighbouring the laundry.
Modern spaces throughout, including a light drenched living area with crisp white walls and split system heating and cooling. This opulent space aptly leads then to the sleek and impressive kitchen, gas stainless steel appliances, dishwasher and stunning floorboards cap things off beautifully. Step outside the undercover outdoor deck is ideal for entertaining friends and family with an unexpected rear backyard that provides ample space and is perfect for the person that wants to downsize yet still enjoys having a yard.
Car accommodation has been well thought of with the brand new remote controlled garage and further space at the front of the property for a second vehicle, boat or caravan storage.
This is an enticing opportunity for any first home buyer, downsizer or investor looking for great return (approx. $380 - $400 per week).
This home offers an outstanding low-upkeep lifestyle in a convenient pocket close to Eastern gardens, waterfront and Central Geelong. With shopping centres, local shops and schools close by, what more could you ask for?! Also, the cosmopolitan cafes of East Geelong only minutes away, and only a 15-minute drive to the Bellarine Peninsula.
Roncon Real Estate An Agency like no other!

Description:
Picture Pretty with Impeccable Style
This neatly packaged period home has everything to surprise and delight the fussiest of buyers. The charming street facade has been lovingly restored and quite modestly conceals the highest of quality renovations awaiting inside. Every inch of this home has been carefully considered and the execution of the finish is even more impressive, perfectly blending the charm of a character home with a modern, stylish and energy-efficient lifestyle.
Upon entry into this home you will quickly become aware of the light, open feeling, the warmth of the hydronic heating and double-glazed windows, soaring high ceilings, custom 2-pack cabinetry and the beautifully polished solid blackbutt flooring throughout. The master bedroom is the first room to witness, with quality built-in robes which stretch to the ceiling, bedside pendant lights, split system air conditioning and feature plantation shutters. The second and third bedroom are spacious and display quality woollen carpets and full length, built in robes.
The heart of the home proudly displays a beautiful modern interior with an impressive formal lounge boasting built in entertaining, perfectly placed timber shelving and additional storage. What is most impressive about this home is the kitchen/dining area with beautiful two-tone cabinetry, fully integrated Siemens oven, induction cooktop, dishwasher and microwave, stone benchtops, feature strip lighting and a breakfast bar with bi-fold windows to the north facing outdoor entertaining, which can be utilized in every season. The modern bathroom provides a shower, free standing bath, feature tiles and quality fittings all bathed in generous amounts of natural light.
The dining area opens via bifold doors to an outdoor entertaining area welcoming the whole family, with spotted gum decking, an electronically controlled Vergola system which opens and closes depending on weather, fantastic lighting and raised planter boxes. Also encompassing a large rear lawn, manicured gardens and side bike or garden shed.
This home really has everything you need for comfort and style. Perfectly located in the esteemed East Geelong, with easy access to the CBD, the Geelong waterfront, Eastern Gardens and the boutique East Geelong shopping and café precinct.

Description:
Huge Potential in Central East
There is beauty in this home waiting to be rejuvenated and unveiled, the astute buyer or renovator will immediately recognise the potential in this property.
Situated on 482sqm (approx.) of land, with north-facing yard and rear access, the size, aspect and location of this property forms the basis of sound investment with further potential to update, extend (stca) and improve its value.
Whilst updates and additions over many years have disguised some of the original features, hints of character still remain, with beautiful pressed metal ceilings and feature walls, picture rails and lining boards awaiting their revival.
Outside, a spacious backyard features established fruit trees and a fantastic north-facing aspect offers a generous outdoor space which presents further opportunity to extend this home (stca). A large shed at the rear provides a generous workshop and/or storage area.
Located in central East Geelong, the position of this home offers fantastic convenience and lifestyle with close proximity to local shopping, parks, CBD and amenities. Points of interest include:
Garden St Cafe precinct - 500m, 6 min walk (approx.)
Eastern Gardens - 700m, 8 min walk (approx.)
Geelong Hospital - 1.2km, 15 min walk, 4 mins drive (approx.)
Geelong Waterfront - 1.3km, 16 min walk, 3 min drive(approx.)
South Geelong Station - 2.1km, 4mins drive (approx.)
This is a fantastic opportunity to create your ultimate home and perfect lifestyle in a central and sought-after location, don't miss out on this one!
Terms: 10% Deposit, 60 day Settlement. For alternative arrangements, please discuss with agent.

Description:
CORNER THIS OPPORTUNITY
Buyers are spoilt for choice with this Newcomb property ripe for renovation or redevelopment on a 660sq m corner block less than 10 minutes drive from Geelongs CBD.
The choice is yours renovate and extend the existing weatherboard house into the massive, sun-soaked allotment of land; renovate the house and subdivide the backyard; or subdivide the whole site for redevelopment.
Location and convenience are key drawcards. The Geelong Botanic Gardens and popular Waterfront precinct are just minutes away, while two nearby shopping strips and the Newcomb Central Shopping Center cater for your local dining and supermarket needs.
Newcomb Library and a selection of schools, including Christ the King Catholic Primary, Newcomb Park Primary and Newcomb Secondary College, are all within the local neighbourhood too.
And if you commute to work, a bus running alongside the property on Charles St will take you to Geelong Railway Station or the CBD.
The home retains many original features from its heydays of the 1960s and 1970s but will need some TLC if its new owners opt to renovate.
But the basics are there a huge main bedroom overlooking the established front garden, two further bedrooms, central bathroom, separate toilet, an L-shaped dining, lounge and kitchen area, and large laundry with an extra shower.
And theres plenty of land to extend to create your dream home. Out the back, a two-room bungalow can provide extra accommodation, alongside a storage shed.
Further afield is a large grassed area full of fruit trees your own summer orchard.
Off-street parking and easy backyard access is available from Charles St.
If you decide to develop the site, the corner block is a massive plus, providing direct street access for any new accommodation.
And when youre done making decisions in this prime part of Newcomb, the nearby Bellarine Highway or Portarlington Rd will take you to the summer playground of the Bellarine Peninsula.

Description:
Move In, Unpack and Relax!
Quite simply there is nothing left to do with this beautifully presented 3 bedroom home set on app. 543sqmin the fastest growing pocket of real estate in the Geelong area. From the updated deck to the well appointed kitchen this stellar property offers so much for the buyer wanting a low maintenance lifestyle without giving up on space to live and breathe and all of this is only 10 minutes from the CBD! The intelligently designed floor plan utilizes the most of the space provided with a versatile open living, dining and kitchen area that greets you upon entry then 3 spacious bedrooms that are all equipped with built in robes and wall to wall carpet plus a neat and clean bathroom with separate shower and bath and single vanity. The real centre piece of the home has to be the lovely deck that overlooks the private rear yard that allows plenty of space for the kids to play or is a fantastic blank canvas for the budding gardener or outdoor enthusiast! Notable extras that set this property apart from the rest are the lovely floating floors, freshly laid carpet and stainless steel cooker plus ceiling fan in the master bedroom and gas furnace and reverse cycle heating and cooling unit in the living room.
The location of the property sells itself with East Geelong TAFE, St. Albans football oval, Buckleys entertainment complex and schools, cafes and shops all located within walking distance plus for those that require public transport theres busses that will take you into the CBD or to the 2 shopping that are located close by.
Make no mistake this fantastic property offers everything that an astute buyer is searching for and with demand as high as it is for quality properties it will not last long. Make time to view and make it yours!
App. Rental $350 per week.
